    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a family of mammals containing around 20 living species in 9 genera, characterized by having a set of bony plates (the carapace) covering much of the body, which is almost hairless in most species.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
